main event: Three or four glowing objects appeared to change in size and made an irregular course in the sky over Brunswick, Maine in 1966.
interesting points: The objects appeared to ascend and descend, and ranged in course from about 5 degrees to 90 degrees in the southeast.
The objects had a steady glow and were visible for about 1.5 minutes.
The objects appeared to be about 3-4 inches in diameter at their largest.
The objects disappeared behind a hill out of sight.
The observer was a 17-year-old civilian who was reported to sound reliable.
result: Possible aircraft, but not definitively explained
